<p style="Normal" xid="2326" props="text-align:left; dom-dir:ltr">considering I had almost died. That was the third time that day, </p>
<p style="Normal" xid="2327" props="text-align:left; dom-dir:ltr">and the sun hadn't even began to set.</p>
<p style="Normal" xid="2328"><c></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="2329" props="text-align:left; dom-dir:ltr">“Ask her,” said Steve with a weary voice.</p>
<p style="Normal" xid="2330"><c></c></p>
<p style="Normal" xid="2331" props="text-align:left; dom-dir:ltr">Though thought is advertised as instant, it does take a little </p>
<p style="Normal" xid="2332" props="text-align:left; dom-dir:ltr">time to formulate in a thing as rudimentary as the human brain. </p>
<p style="Normal" xid="2333" props="text-align:left; dom-dir:ltr">In that time, Eileen had already spoken to me, saying the exact </p>
<p style="Normal" xid="2334" props="text-align:left; dom-dir:ltr">same thing.</p>
<p style="Normal" xid="2335"><c></c></p>
